<br>
That said, Aroth, some of your arguments are REALLY out of place on the warrior boards. Yep, the mitigation nerf + PoP unbalanced monks, and they had to live for 6 months in a rather unfortunate state, and a lot of your 13 year-olds on monkly business nearly wet their beds (again) over it. But, keep this in mind, warriors have been calling for fixes for 15 months now. 15 MONTHS, 15 months of posts and pleading with no results. Before PoP, we were competing for the tanking spot with paladins, Sk's and monks. With the introduction of PoP, we only had to compete with pallies and SK's, but both classes have become significantly better than us in XP tanking. At this point, if you read other m-boards, you will notice a decrease in people's desire for having warriors as tanks due to the agro issue.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, you got your mitigation partially un-nerfed, congrats. But this is the wrong board to come justifying the fix because of how broken monks were. We know what it's like to be broken. Our primary role in XP groups has beeb diminished in favor of other classes to oblivion, to the point where some will simply not group with warriors anymore unless defensive is specifically required. So, don't come here justifying your previously broken status on the boards of a class who has been equally broken for a far longer time frame. Especially consdering the promise thats VI would look into warrior agro was loaded, and their promised adjustments for melee classes served as nothing more than a monk fix.<br>
