<br>
One post on here was a reply as to why monks need mitigation for pulling, and it was stated that avoidence does nothing when running.  If you paid attention to the same persons post, he mentioned that he thought they should make avoidence the same from behind as it is from in front.  If you did get a fix like that, and a boost to avoidence, then why would you need mitigation?  I would be all for a fix like <br>
that.<br>
<br>
Just want to state one thing again.  I witnessed a 58 monk tanking in PoP without uber gear.  It does work.  It is NOT efficient, but please, stop with the bs saying it couldn't happen.  Yes things were bad, and I agree that a fix was needed, but I think a lot of people are saying it was a lot worse than it was.<br>
<br>
About solo.  I see no reason why a monk could run around without ever needing to stop, as a mend ever 6 mins was enough to keep them healed.  Yet warriors need a lot more in terms of gear to solo, and still not do so near as well.  You ask why shouldn't a monk be allowed to solo, well, why should they?  I personally have no problem with them soloing some, but just playing devils advocate, why should they have been allowed to continue to solo so much better?  Though it's a non issue in PoP, just thought I'd throw that in.  Of course, back before the nerf, I was happy that monks solo'd, since it would give me a better chance as getting a group as a tank.<br>
I really don't mind monks soloing some, but being able to do it so much better than other pure melee (ever seen a rogue try to solo?), imo, it was overpowered before the first nerf.<br>
