<br>
A great idea. I'd have loved it if they had gone in that direction.<br>
<br>
They didn't. But so far what they did do helps with the pulling and didn't overpower monk mitigation.<br>
<br>
RE: How max hits sucked ass for pulling ...<br>
<br>
As Tempur mentioned ... the max hits from behind, the stuns, the continued max hits from behind, basically, I'd get stuck with my back to the mob, and unable to move. Meaning I couldn't PULL the mob. Then I'd be dead.<br>
<br>
Sometimes I'd just pull in a different view with my face to the mob and it'd help. But then I run slower by backpedaling, and I'd still get dead.<br>
<br>
Rock ... meet hard place.<br>
<br>
Yeah, sure your suggestion would have been great, as it would have fixed that problem wonderfully.<br>
<br>
But what they did also fixed the problem.<br>
<br>
RE: Monk tanking.<br>
<br>
I've tanked in PoP tier 1 since level 57, as a monk. All post-nerf.<br>
<br>
I know it's possible.<br>
<br>
I also know what makes it possible ... SLOW.<br>
<br>
Unslowed, it's just way too much of a mana drain.<br>
<br>
But, you know, I don't want to tank. I log on my monk, I'm not looking to tank. So that aspect of PoP never bothered me in the least.<br>
<br>
It's when I went out to split and pull the mobs and I started going splat that I got miffed with the way the &quot;nerf&quot; happened.<br>
<br>
RE: Monk soloing.<br>
<br>
It wasn't monk defense that allowed them to solo. Monks could and did still solo POST nerf.<br>
<br>
What allows monks to solo are these things:<br>
<br>
DPS. Monks have pretty high DPS. So toe-to-toe, monk versus one single mob, a monk has a good chance to kick the living snot out of it. That's sort of in line with what the class is supposed to be, imo.<br>
<br>
LOW Hit Points: It takes a LOT less downtime to recover 2500 hit points than it does 3 to 4k.<br>
<br>
As part of the low hit points thing ... a fungi tunic, which is rather needed for melees to solo with any level of efficiency, has a much more powerful effect on a monk because the regen is a higher percentage of their hit points per tick.<br>
<br>
Mend: Every six minutes, a monk can self heal. This isn't all that broken, but when combined with good regen, like a fungi, along with low hit points, it just becomes EFFICIENT. And for soloing, it's all about maximizing this kind of crap.<br>
<br>
Epic Clicky Haste. The ability to go from, say, 21 percent item haste on an FBSS, to 62 percent haste, from the epic click stacking, siginificantly increases a monk's ability to solo.<br>
<br>
If a warrior wanted to solo, what they ought to do is ... get a Windblade (on my server, a windblade costs now, what most Tstaffs used to cost Pre-PoP) ... get a ToD (monks don't even GET a slow proccing weapon) ... get a Fungi (yeah, I know, not everyone can do this, but not every monk can do this either), DROP their unbuffed Hit Points down substantially (2500 hit points is more than enough to tank a velk's spider) ... and get an eyepatch of plunder (which is no harder to acquire than the monk epic, and just as useful).<br>
<br>
Or not.<br>
<br>
Seriously, if you WANT to solo, you can solo.<br>
<br>
Personally, I play my warrior a lot more than my monk right now (even with the latest patch). It's just five zillion times more fun to be a tank. It's way more fun to actually group with people, and dungeon crawl or grind XP with friends in a group. So while some warriors may envy the monk who solo's ... lemme just say that from a monk who has solo'd a LOT for 60 levels, I envied the FUN my warrior friends had PLAYING EVERQUEST so much that I went and made a warrior.<br>
<br>
Warriors have problems. A lot of them. And the deaf ear that Sony has turned to the class is annoying. And the fact that all they ever get out of each new expansion is more gear (which everyone else also gets), is kind of sad.<br>
<br>
But believe me ... warriors are a very fun class to play, and soloing is SUCK ASS BORING!<br>
<br>
