General point is this...don't class bash and propogate hate because one class can do something better than another class.  That other class also has some weaknesses that can be a serious pain...and if YOU don't play it you probably have not a clue what it takes to overcome it.  All you see is &quot;how great they are&quot; and nothing else.  Think before you speak...or better yet...roll up the class you are about to bash and level him up so you actually know what you are talking about.<br>
<br>
Everybody knows you pretty much have to beat SoE over the head to get things fixed that NEED to be fixed.  Warriors are but one small voice screaming for attention.  Rather than alienate yourselves (ourselves since I rather enjoy playing my warrior also) from the other classes, show some joy towards them for overcoming nerfs...and then enlist them in YOUR cause to get YOUR problems fixed.  Just imagine how much that small voice of warriors would be amplified if that voice were repeated by Monks...and Enchanters...and Paladins...etc.  It wouldn't take long before SoE had little choice but to address the problems.<br>
<br>
It's easy to whine and moan because you THINK the grass is greener below the feet of another class...but it's a lot smarter to garner their support for your cause than it is to hammer them because of a perception that they have something you don't. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chongdamonk>Chongdamonk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/11/03 5:01:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2052.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What made me crazy</span><hr size=1> I'm not uber, and I could tank in the planes during the nerf and after.  The main point is monks do not want to tank.  It's just not mana efficient.  We just want to survive a pull, and receiving some of our mitigation back makes that somewhat easier.  Being a pure melee I would like to be able to take a few hits though.  Like the previous poster said, if you have no extended experience playing a monk, then you really have no room to comment on what monks can and cannot do, and what you have seen and heard monks do.<br>
Warriors need some tweaking..that's for sure.  I don't disagree with that at all.  But then many classes do in one way or another.<br>
Soloing...I account that to having an epic with 40 percent haste that stacks with item haste.  Not something you can really blame on a monk's ability to tank.  If you had 76% self haste and wore a fungi you could solo too.  Before PoP came out I had seen all level 60 pure melee classes soloing, I never thought much of it.  They all wore fungis though.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
